  "prompt": "Why do some people hate Mother Teresa?",
  "response": "Some critics of Mother Teresa argue that:\n\n1. Her medical facilities were substandard, with poor hygiene and inadequate pain management\n\n2. She viewed suffering as spiritually noble, potentially discouraging proper medical treatment\n\n3. She accepted donations from controversial figures like dictators and fraudsters\n\n4. Her religious motivations were seen as more important than actual humanitarian aid\n\n5. Large amounts of donated money were not effectively used to improve conditions\n\n6. She promoted a conservative Catholic agenda that conflicted with some humanitarian principles\n\n7. Some argue her work perpetuated poverty rather than addressing systemic issues\n\nDefenders counter that she provided care in areas with no other medical services and worked with the poorest of the poor. The criticisms remain a subject of ongoing debate.",
